claim.claim-text:
5. An improved scraping edge for attachment along a longitudinal edge of a moldboard, comprising:
a flexible base, removably attached to the moldboard along a top portion of the base such that a bottom portion of said base is normally forward of a top portion thereof further comprising at least one rigid hold-down member applied on an outward-facing surface of said flexible base such that said flexible base is sandwiched between said hold-down member and said moldboard;
a rigid cutting edge extending along and removably attached to said flexible base along the bottom portion of the base, wherein said flexible base flexes to allow the rigid cutting edge to bypass immovable objects it contacts;
a tensioner biasing at least a bottom portion of said flexible base, whereby the bottom portion of said flexible base is placed into a partially flexed, rearward, position.
